!! Feature Plugins

These add extra superpowers to your editor!

!!! Auto Close Tags
When you type `<div>`, it automatically adds `</div>` for you. Works with HTML tags and TiddlyWiki widgets like `<$list>`. Saves you tons of typing!

!!! Click Navigate
Hold Ctrl (or Cmd on Mac) and click on a link to jump right to that tiddler. Shift+Ctrl+Click opens it in a new window. Super handy for navigating around!

!!! Link Preview
Hover your mouse over a link and see a preview of what's inside that tiddler without clicking. Shows the title, tags, and a bit of the content.

!!! Code Folding
Got a long piece of code or a big widget? Click the little arrow to collapse it and hide the details. Click again to expand. Keeps things tidy!

!!! Line Numbers
Shows line numbers on the left side of the editor. Also highlights the line you're currently on so you don't lose your place.

!!! Emoji Picker
Type `:` and start typing an emoji name (like `:smile:`) to get emoji suggestions! Pick one and it inserts the emoji for you.

!!! User Snippets
Create shortcuts for text you type often. For example, make "hw" expand into "Hello, World!". Great for templates and repeated content.

!!! Lint (Error Checker)
Finds potential problems in your code, like:
* Forgetting to close a widget (`<$list>` without `</$list>`)
* Unclosed brackets or links
* Undefined macros, procedures, or variables
* Unknown widgets or filter operators
* Shows little warning marks so you can fix issues
* Click on warnings for quick-fix suggestions!

!!! Image Preview
When you write `[img[picture.png]]`, you'll see a preview of the image right there in the editor!

!!! Color Picker
See a color code like `#ff0000`? A little colored square appears next to it. Click it to open a color picker and change the color easily!

!!! Word Count
Shows how many words, characters, and lines your tiddler has. When you select text, it shows you the count for just that selection too.

!!! Zen Mode
Distraction-free writing! Hides everything except your text so you can focus. Features:
* Clean, centered writing area
* Typewriter mode (keeps your line in the middle of the screen)
* Can hide everything except what you're typing

!!! Plugin Combiner
Bundles multiple CodeMirror 6 plugins into a single combined plugin. Great for distributing a pre-configured setup or creating a minimal installation package. Just select the plugins you want and export!

---

!! Keyboard Plugins

!!! Vim Keymap
For people who love the Vim text editor. Uses special keyboard commands like pressing `j` to go down, `k` to go up, and `:w` to save. It's weird at first but super fast once you learn it!

!!! Emacs Keymap
For fans of the Emacs text editor. Uses Ctrl-based shortcuts like Ctrl+A to go to the start of a line and Ctrl+E to go to the end.

---

!! Toolbar Styles

This plugin gives you 10 different looks for the toolbar buttons (the buttons above the editor for bold, italic, etc.). Pick from simple and clean to fancy and colorful!

---

!! How to Use These Plugins

# ''Install the main editor plugin'' - This is required for everything else
# ''Pick a theme'' - Choose colors you like
# ''Add language plugins'' - If you write code, add the languages you use
# ''Add feature plugins'' - Pick the extra features you want

!! Settings

Most plugins have settings you can change in the Control Panel. Look for "CodeMirror 6" in the settings to:
* Turn features on/off
* Change how things work
* Customize the editor to your liking

---

!! Keyboard Shortcuts

Here are some handy shortcuts that work in the editor:

| !Shortcut | !What it does |
| `Ctrl+B` | Bold text |
| `Ctrl+I` | Italic text |
| `Ctrl+Z` | Undo |
| `Ctrl+Y` or `Ctrl+Shift+Z` | Redo |
| `Ctrl+F` | Find text |
| `Ctrl+H` | Find and replace |
| `Ctrl+/` | Toggle comment |
| `Ctrl+Space` | Trigger autocomplete |
| `Tab` | Indent (or accept autocomplete) |
| `Shift+Tab` | Unindent |
| `Ctrl+Click` | Add another cursor |
| `Ctrl+D` | Select next occurrence |
| `Alt+ArrowUp/Down` | Move line up/down |
| `Ctrl+Shift+K` | Delete line |
| `Ctrl+Enter` | Insert line below |
| `Ctrl+Shift+Enter` | Insert line above |
| `Ctrl+[` / `Ctrl+]` | Indent less/more |
| `Escape` | Close autocomplete/dialogs |

---

!! Questions?

If something doesn't work or you're confused:
1. Make sure the main editor plugin is installed
2. Check that the plugin is enabled in settings
3. Try refreshing the page
4. Check the browser console for error messages (press F12)

Happy writing!
